children.text:
Disclaimer:
This app is an undergraduate project for MIE350 at the University of Toronto. Please exercise caution when following any recommendations made by this app and consult a doctor for any decisions related to sleep and activity.

Purpose and functionalities:
This is a sleep tracker app that aims to help people keep track of how long they sleep, the quality of their sleep, and any additional notes about what may have impacted their sleep. Recommendations for when the user should sleep are also given. Users have the ability to create an account using their name, date of birth, username, email, and password. After creating an account and logging in, users can input sleep data (length, feelings/mood, comments) and activity data (caffeine intake, calorie intake, workouts). This information can be summarized and viewed through various plots.

{{"You should get " + getRecommendation.data.sleepAmount + " hours of sleep!"}}

Did you know that 33% of Canadians aged 18-64 do not meet the recommended sleep duration? Getting enough sleep can help you better remember the information you've learned, improve immunity, and  control hunger through producing hormones. 

In order to get better sleep, wwe recommend increasing daily physical activity and maintaining a healthy sleep schedule.

To learn more about the benefits of cultivating a healthy sleep habit and improving sleep quality, please visit the websites below!
